Algorithm for game 1 (connect 4)
1-define the board size ( 7 columns and 6 rows)
2-specify game board object
3-numbering the columns
4-print the slots of the game board
5-search bottom up for an open slot
6-make a function to define players (x – o)
7-define all the directions to check
8-search outwards looking for matching pieces
9-check possible direction pairs for ‘4 pieces in a row’  
10-if didn’t find any winner return False
11-initialize the game board
12-ask the user for input, but only accept valid turns
13-end the game if there is a winner
14-end the game if it is draw 
